V1.0
feat(toolchain): expand VZ CLI suite, packaging, docs, and reliability hardening

- Added cross-platform build improvements:
  - new `windows64` target (MinGW x86_64)
  - new `windows-all` convenience target (32-bit + 64-bit)
  - updated `build-all`/`package-all` to include Win64
  - improved help/BUILD docs to match current targets

- Added install/uninstall workflow:
  - `make install` / `make uninstall`
  - supports `PREFIX` and `DESTDIR`
  - installs binaries + project docs
  - avoids forcing package generation during install

- Centralized versioning:
  - added top-level `VERSION` (set to `1.0`)
  - Makefile injects `TOOL_VERSION` into all binaries
  - all tools now support `--version` / `-V`
  - usage/help text updated accordingly

- Expanded `vzpack` capabilities:
  - accepts out-of-order Intel HEX / SREC records
  - detects sparse ranges and requires explicit `--fill/-f` to pack holes
  - keeps overlap/conflict checks strict
  - improved diagnostics/output summaries

- Updated roadmap/docs organization:
  - moved TODO section into dedicated `TODO.md`
  - linked TODO from README
  - added roadmap items for `.cvz` support and a third disk-format tool (`vzdisk`, working name)

- Licensing/provenance cleanup:
  - added `UNLICENSE` and `NOTICE`
  - clarified scope for third-party/inherited code in README/TEXT2BAS docs
  - added explicit provenance wording for reverse-engineered origins
  - included `UNLICENSE`/`NOTICE` in package/install doc staging

- Documentation refresh:
  - README intro now frames project as a complete CLI toolset
  - removed redundant status text
  - aligned BUILD/README with current commands and behavior

- Reliability and memory-safety fixes:
  - fixed overlapping-copy UB (`strcpy` -> `memmove`) in tokenization/squeeze paths
    in `text2bas` and `vzpack`
  - added bounds checks for `text2bas` filename handling
  - fixed partial-allocation cleanup path in `vzpack` addrmap init

- Validation:
  - completed end-to-end round-trip checks across:
    `text2bas -> vz2wav -> wav2vz -> vzexport -> vzpack`
  - payloads match across bin/hex/srec/bas repack paths
  - sanitizer runs (ASan/UBSan) completed clean in this environment
